provide a rational basis to understand the impact of metal ions on amyloid fibril aggregation and morphology. The current study expands the bioinorganic facet of AD and other tauopathies, and it underscores the importance of metal-tau interactions as potential therapeutic targets in these neurodegenerative diseases.", 'summary_1': ''}
