er intrathecal injection in combination with crystalloid co-loading, with rescue vasopressors titrated according to maternal haemodynamics. For newly identified WPW, contemporary recommendations support risk stratification, including assessment for intermittent pre-excitation, and consideration of electrophysiological evaluation and catheter ablation when clinically indicated.', 'summary_1': ''}
