 a dominant m.2356C\u2009>\u2009G clone correlated with POLR2A activation and widespread transcriptional amplification, consistent with a mitochondria-nucleus signaling axis contributing to adverse prognosis in this cancer type. Collectively, these findings establish MitoBayes as a robust statistical framework linking mitochondrial genetic diversity to disease phenotypes and highlight mitochondrial clonal selection as a mechanistically and clinically actionable target for therapeutic and diagnostic development.", 'summary_1': ''}
