ubstitution patterns, hydrogen-bonding capacity, and lipophilicity. Several scaffolds demonstrate validated binding with submicromolar affinity (K d ≈ 0.11-0.17 μM); however, major gaps remain in achieving robust NR4A selectivity, establishing blood-brain barrier (BBB) penetration, and demonstrating consistent in vivo efficacy. Overall, this analysis highlights both the promise and the persistent challenges in developing Nurr1-targeted therapeutics for neurodegenerative disease intervention.", 'summary_1': ''}
